Delphine Arnault appointed Director at LVMH main board - LVMH
https://www.lvmh.com/news-documents/press-releases/delphine-arnault-appointed-director-at-lvmh-main-board/






Sender*





Recipient(s)*


Multiple recipients? Separate the addresses with a comma.



Message

















Share








 


The board of LVMH, the world’s leading luxury products group, announces the appointment of Delphine Arnault as Director of the Group.
Born on April 4, 1975, Delphine Arnault graduated from EDHEC business school and the London School of Economics before beginning her career with the international management consultancy firm McKinsey.
In 2000, she was part of the development of John Galliano’s company where she gained a solid grounding in fashion. In 2001, she became a director of Christian Dior where she managed many product ranges, contributing to their exceptional commercial success worldwide; she also sits on the management board of Loewe where she is responsible for product strategy.
This appointment follows that of Arnaud Lagardère who joined the LVMH board at the last Annual General Meeting.












 

