Delphine Arnault investing in new designer labels





      Thu, October 17, 2013    


Delphine Arnault, daughter of LVMH chairman and CEO Bernard Arnault, is investing in new designer labels to compensate for declining sales of the company's flagship Louis Vuitton brand, the Wall Street Journal reported.
Delphine Arnault is also in charge of all products at Luis Vuitton, the article said. She is involved in hiring the designer who will succeed Marc Jacobs at Vuitton.
LVMH includes several well-known, old luxury brands "that have struggled to regain their original luster," the Journal article said. The report noted that bringing on new labels requires a smaller investment but can divert management attention.  (Source: Wall Street Journal, Oct. 17, 2013.)

