Executive Profile
Delphine Arnault Gancia  Executive Vice President of Louis Vuitton and Director, LVMH Moët Hennessy Louis Vuitton S.E.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 6 different industries.See Board Relationships42€2,511,258As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Ms. Delphine Arnault Gancia has been an Executive Vice President of Louis Vuitton Malletier at LVMH Moët Hennessy Louis Vuitton SA since September 2013 and oversees all product-related activities. Ms. Gancia serves on the Management Board of Loewe SA, where she is responsible for product strategy. She served as a Deputy General Manager of Christian Dior Couture from 2008 to 2013. She served as an Executive Officer of Emilio Pucci S.r.l. She was a Consultant at McKinsey ... & Company before joining Christian Dior Couture in 2001. In 2000, she was part of the development of John Galliano's company, where she gained a solid grounding in fashion. Ms. Gancia has been an Independent Director at Twenty-First Century Fox, Inc. since June 28, 2013. She has been an Independent Member of Supervisory Board at Métropole Télévision SA since November 5, 2009. She has been a Director of Christian Dior SE since April 5, 2012. She has been an Independent Director of Havas SA since June 5,2013. She has been a Director of LVMH Moët Hennessy Louis Vuitton SA since October 3, 2003 and of several of its subsidiaries including Loewe SA, Emilio Pucci Srl, Les Echos, Château Cheval Blanc and Céline. Ms. Gancia graduated from EDHEC Business School and the London School of Economics.Read Full Background




